  "prompt": "I did really bad on my 1st term of 11th (cbse).If I pull myself together and do really well on the other 2 terms can I still get above 95% at the end?",
  "response": "Yes, you can still achieve above 95% in your CBSE 11th grade if you work hard and perform well in the other two terms. Here\u2019s how you can approach it:\n\n### 1. **Analyze Your Performance**\n   - Identify the areas where you struggled in the first term.\n   - Focus on improving your weak topics by revising thoroughly and practicing more.\n\n### 2. **Set Realistic Goals**\n   - Break down your syllabus for the remaining terms and set weekly or monthly goals.\n   - Aim for consistent high scores in the upcoming assessments.\n\n### 3. **Focus on Concept Clarity**\n   - Ensure you understand the concepts thoroughly, especially in subjects like Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics.\n   - Use NCERT textbooks as your primary resource and solve additional practice questions.\n\n### 4. **Practice Regularly**\n   - Solve previous years\u2019 question papers and sample papers to get familiar with the exam pattern.\n   - Focus on time management and accuracy during practice.\n\n### 5. **Seek Help if Needed**\n   - If you\u2019re struggling with certain topics, don\u2019t hesitate to ask your teachers or consider additional tutoring.\n   - Use online resources like YouTube channels or educational apps for extra help.\n\n### 6. **Stay Consistent**\n   - Avoid procrastination and maintain a regular study schedule.\n   - Stay motivated by reminding yourself of your goal to achieve above 95%.\n\n### 7. **Improve Exam Strategy**\n   - Pay attention to how you attempt questions in exams. Focus on neatness, clarity, and avoiding mistakes.\n   - Allocate time wisely during exams to ensure you complete all sections.\n\n### 8. **Utilize All Assessments**\n   - Perform well in unit tests, practical exams, and other internal assessments, as they also contribute to your final marks.\n\n### Final Thoughts\nThe CBSE system allows for improvement across terms, so a strong performance in the second and third terms can significantly boost your overall percentage. Stay focused, work hard, and don\u2019t let the first term\u2019s results demotivate you. With consistent effort, achieving above 95% is definitely possible!",
